@tonyh6309 I hope you understand that Mars helicopter video on his channel right now is a second and revised and he didn't flinch before deleting the first one within a few hours of people calling him out, then posting another like nothing happened. 

He literally pointed out how stupid it was to fly a craft through mars's thin atmosphere and did his own vacuum chamber test to show how he had debunked the craft, but he was wrong. 

I used to be his biggest fan, but after that I  started questioning his motifs in general.

@dalemsilas8425  But curiously you seem to be the *only* person on the internet who 'knows' that Thunderfoot replaced his 1st video. 

Even more surprising that none of those who called out his first (replaced) video would have bothered to comment on such an egregious act. He must have done a remarkable job of cleaning up the internet removing all the comments which would have lit up youtube, Reddit etc. from aggrieved viewers.

I'm sure we would all be grateful if you would provide any evidence for your claim as it would seriously change my opinion of him.

@tonyh6309  FYI I didn't say people called him out "on changing the video," I said they called him out on his mistakes, comments which you might probably still find, I bet mine is still there.

That's why you have a kind of confusion because some people remember him saying something very different at certain points, called out his mistakes... but suddenly the video appeared to contradict these comments.

... and yes I remembered a few people did call him out for editing the video, which is how I noticed it.
